      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AMAHNI'S GIRL (1) led into the straight before fading to run fourth over 1830m at Eagle Farm. Expected to run the trip in this easier class with Spokes' claim. Leading prospect. CHAMPAGNE ROUGE (5) is a distance and track specialist who motored late from back in the field with a sound third over 2230m at this track. Finds a suitable race and can find the winner's circle. Senior rider hops aboard and should get the right tempo. YUKANUMA (3) tough old gelding ready for this trip. Savaged the line when fourth over 1800m at the Gold Coast. Key jockey change and has a good record at this track. Each way. ALABAMA GIRL (8) back in trip with a respectable sixth over 1608m here. Expected to run the journey and gets map favours.",
